<dl id="n41039a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41039a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41039a"> 39(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> lends clothes / to <font face="wake">A</font> <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n41039a"><li>FW 243.12 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kd/lexkd.htm#n41039a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kd/l39kd.htm#n41039a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n41039a">MS BL 47477-98</ms> </li><li>JJA 51:194 <a name="kad5" href="../../ff/fdra/kda.htm#kdd6">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kd/kdd6.htm#n41039a">Draft: II.1&sect;4.6</a> </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Transferred via <a name="sh1013c" href="sh1all.htm#sh1013c">Sheet i-13(c)</a> to <a name="sh1027c" href="sh1all.htm#sh1027c">Sheet i-27(c)</a>. Not in 1939 text. </mm> <blockquote class="sources">A husband is obliged to keep his wife adequately supplied with clothing but this obligation is sufficiently fulfilled if <mark>he merely lends the clothing to her</mark> so that it remains his property; her creditors could not in such a case take the clothing in satisfaction of a judgement against the wife. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 38</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
